<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1901,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[199,251,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">Egg.</emphasis>
Description based on uterine eggs from pregnant female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Whitish" authorityName="Whitish" box="[934,1193,1901,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="judicariae">
<emphasis box="[934,1085,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="33">D. judicariae</emphasis>
: Whitish
</taxonomicName>
, relatively slender (c. 1.5 x 0.3 mm), cylindrical, long axis barely curved in lateral view, rounded at posterior end, tapering and somewhat truncate at anterior (micropylar) end. Chorion ornamented with fine ridges forming hexagonal reticulations, dorsally without a hatching pleat delimited by raised ridges.
</paragraph>
